# Project Instructions for Claude Code

## Documentation
- Always keep README.md up to date when adding new features or making significant changes
- Update the Features section to reflect new capabilities
- Add examples to the Demo section when new functionality is added
- Keep the Configuration section in sync with the actual routines.json structure

## Code Style
- Use German for task names and user-facing text (this is a German family routine app)
- Follow existing patterns for routine configuration in public/routines.json
- Maintain consistent color coding across similar tasks in different routines

## Commit Messages
- Follow the existing commit style: brief, descriptive, imperative mood
- Always include Co-Authored-By line for commits made with Claude
